However, at high concentration, the SV curve deviates from the linear correlation with the increase of concentration (Fig.S12), indicating that both static and dynamic quenching processes exist [54,55]. Especially, compared with most of the recently reported fluorescence methods for detecting Pb2+, this method possessed a comparative or relatively lower detection limit and wider linear range (
